<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   SPD Rejects Participation in UN Combat Missions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SPD Rejects Participation in UN Combat Missions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804114294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1100 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804114294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The Social Democrats [SPD] will 
not agree to the Bundeswehr's participation in UN combat 
missions under any circumstances. SPD Chairman Rudolf Scharping 
made it clear in Bonn today that his party's political position 
will not change, even when the legal disputes have been 
clarified before the Federal Constitutional Court. 
  Following his return from a trip to the United States, 
Scharping said in Bonn that he assumes the judges in Karlsruhe 
will insist on involving the Bundestag in a decision on the 
participation of German servicemen in UN missions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

