<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel `Firmly Against' Bundeswehr Reduction Plans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel `Firmly Against' Bundeswehr Reduction Plans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1804150994 Hamburg BILD in German 18 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1804150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg BILD </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Einar Koch report: "Kinkel: Do Not Save on the </F>
Bundeswehr"] 
  [Text] An open quarrel has broken out in the government 
coalition in Bonn about the future of the Bundeswehr! 
  Free Democratic Party Chairman and Foreign Minister Klaus 
Kinkel is firmly against plans by Defense Minister Volker Ruehe 
to reduce the strength of the Bundeswehr from 370,000 to 320,000. 
  Kinkel told BILD: "The Bundeswehr finally needs planning 
security, and for the families as well. In the long run, the 
discussion cannot be such that one says: We have such and such 
an amount of money, and for that we can afford such and such a 
Bundeswehr. If I had my say, the decided strength of 370,000 
should be maintained if at all possible. I do see the financial 
problems, but in this case one has to reexamine all other 
possibilities of saving money." 
  Ruehe wants to present his concept for the Bundeswehr to the 
Bundestag this week. 

</TEXT>

