<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Sweden </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anti-EU Groups Form Umbrella Organization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anti-EU Groups Form Umbrella Organization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1804120494 Paris AFP in English 0905 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1804120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stockholm, April 18 (AFP) -- Fourteen Swedish 
organizations opposed to joining the European Union [EU] have 
formed an umbrella organization to campaign against EU 
membership in a referendum scheduled for November 13. 
  Organizers said the new body, which does not yet have a 
name, 
intends to provide every Swedish household with anti-EU 
information in the run-up to the vote. 
  Included in the organization are the anti-EU factions of the 
Social Democrat, Center and Christian Democrats as well as the 
Left Party and Green Party. 
  The umbrella organization has demanded at least 98 million 
kronor (12.5 million dollars) in state campaign funds. 
  Sweden concluded its membership negotiations in March and is 
scheduled for entry into the EU on January 1, 1995 along with 
Finland, Austria, and Norway. 
  But Swedish opposition to the union is strong. 
  According to the most recent poll published in the 
GOETEBORGS 
POSTEN daily on Sunday [16 April], 42 percent of Swedes are 
opposed to membership, while 33 percent are in favour and 25 
percent are undecided. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

