<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas Decries Changes to Varosha Map </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denktas Decries Changes to Varosha Map </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1704140694 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1030 GMT 17 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1704140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Rauf Denktas has said that the 
nondocument on the confidence-building measures [CBM's] has been 
further damaged as a result of the violation of the map during 
the last round of the talks. Replying to a question by a 
Turkish Cypriot News Agency correspondent on whether any results 
were achieved during his visit to Maras [Varosha] yesterday, 
Denktas said that he did not go to Maras to achieve results but 
to see what the two maps submitted by the United Nations were 
about and to determine whether the sections requested in the 
second map were actually within the barbed wire region. He 
added that the sections requested in the second map were not 
remotely connected with the barbed wire region. 
  Commenting on the Greek Cypriot shots fired at Turkish 
Cypriot positions on the border, Denktas noted that it is clear 
that provocations are increasing in all fields. He stressed 
that the side that is wrong and knows it to be so is escalating 
the provocations. Pointing out that it is the duty of the just 
to be patient and coolheaded, Denktas added: I, therefore, 
sincerely congratulate our soldiers and their commanders who 
have maintained their patience, discipline, and their cool in 
the face of these provocations. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

