<H3> <TI>   Spokesman on Attacks on Istanbul Patriarchate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman on Attacks on Istanbul Patriarchate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1604184894 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1700 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1604184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Late last night vandals broke the windows of an 
all-girls school close to the Greek school in Istanbul and the 
Ecumenical Patriarch's quarters at Fanari. This incident is one 
of a series of others that have occurred recently against the 
Ecumenical Patriarchate in Istanbul. 
  Threatening slogans were written on the walls of the 
Patriarchate and there were repeated attempts to set fires. 
Replying to a question on whether the government made any 
representations on the attack against the all-girl school at 
Fanari, Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said the 
government always makes the necessary diplomatic 
representations. We do not know to what extent official Turkish 
policy is reflected in these recent events. Venizelos repeated 
that Turkey should prove that it has some kind of relation to 
what is called European civilization. 

</TEXT>

