<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Tells Yeltsin Bloodshed in Gorazde Must Stop </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Tells Yeltsin Bloodshed in Gorazde Must Stop </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904105394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1003 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- In a telephone conversation with 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin, Chancellor Helmut Kohl has 
stressed that the bloodshed in the east Bosnian town of Gorazde 
must be stopped. "Every effort must be made" to bring this 
about, Kohl told Yeltsin this morning, according to government 
spokesman Dieter Vogel. 
  The chancellor called for a lasting peace settlement in the 
region. Kohl talked to U.S. President Bill Clinton and French 
President Francois Mitterrand about the situation in Gorazde by 
telephone yesterday. 

</TEXT>

