<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ahtisaari Confirms Participation in PFP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ahtisaari Confirms Participation in PFP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804164894 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1430 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1804164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Martti Ahtisaari has confirmed Finland's 
participation in NATO's Partnership for Peace [PFP] program. 
The PFP agreement will be signed later, apparently at the same 
time as Sweden. In its decision to approve the agreement, the 
government stresses that Finland will chiefly take part in 
peacekeeping training, rescue work, and environmental 
protection. The government also points out that Finland is not 
seeking new defense solutions through the PFP. 

</TEXT>

