<F P=106> [Article signed JWI: "Palestine: European Money for the </F>
Palestinian Police Force"] 
  [Text] Luxembourg, 19 Apr (BELGA) -- The European Union 
[EU] will contribute ECU10 million to the establishment of the 
Palestinian police force in Gaza and Jericho following the 
decision of the European foreign ministers meeting in Luxembourg 
today. 
  Belgian Foreign Minister Willy Claes briefly reported on his 
meeting last Wednesday [13 April] with PLO leader 'Arafat at the 
Council of Europe in Strasbourg. 
  During that meeting Mr. 'Arafat had emphasized the need for 
quick and specific assistance for Gaza and Jericho, which will 
shortly have an independent Palestinian administration. 
