<H3> <TI>   Kohl Discusses Situation in Gorazde With Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Discusses Situation in Gorazde With Yeltsin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904110094 Hamburg DPA in German 1017 GMT 19 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1904110094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl on Tuesday 
morning [19 April] discussed the situation in Gorazde with 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin over the phone. As government 
spokesman Dieter Vogel said, they talked about a potential 
solution by means of negotiations and a cease-fire in the 
interest of the civilian population. 
  Kohl affirmed his view that "all efforts must be made to put 
an end to the bloodshed in the region and to bring about a 
lasting peace settlement." On Monday, Kohl had telephoned U.S. 
President Bill Clinton and French President Francois Mitterrand. 

</TEXT>

