<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "More Than 140 Caught in Northern </F>
Anti-Mafia Operation"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Milan, April 18 -- More than 140 people were 
arrested in pre-dawn raids around the northern city of Milan and 
in several southern regions in a police operation code-named 
Scorched Earth, aimed against organized crime groups 
specializing in arms and drug trafficking, robbery and fencing 
stolen goods, police announced Monday [18 April]. 
  Police carried out more than 300 searches and confiscated an 
unspecified number of weapons, drugs and ammunition in the 
raids, which were a follow-up to Operation North-South which a 
few months ago struck at the drug and arms pipeline between 
south and north. 
  Most of the arrests, police said, were made in the northern 
region of Lombardy and in the poorer outskirts of Milan, where 
drug dealers are most active. 

</TEXT>

