<H3> <TI>   Lists Conditions for Talks With India </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lists Conditions for Talks With India </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1904162994 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 
1600 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1904162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Talks between the prime minister, Ms. Benazir 
Bhutto, and the German chancellor, Mr. Helmut Kohl, were held in 
Bonn today. The two leaders are understood to have discussed 
bilateral relations as well as regional and international 
issues. The talks were marked by extreme warmth and cordiality 
which are the hallmark of the relations between Pakistan and 
Germany. 
  During the talks, the prime minister is understood to have 
put forward a number of proposals for expanding economic 
cooperation between the two countries. She also briefed the 
chancellor about the latest situation in occupied Kashmir and 
reiterated Pakistan's firm belief that the Kashmir dispute could 
be resolved only by the grant of right of self-determination to 
the Kashmiris. She said Pakistan was ready to enter into a 
dialogue with India provided it lifts the siege of Hazratbal 
Shrine, puts an end to the ongoing repression, and considerably 
reduces the presence of its troops in occupied Kashmir. 
  The talks continued during the luncheon hosted by the German 
chancellor in honor of the prime minister. 

</TEXT>

