<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Popular Party Rejects Joint Opposition With PDS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Popular Party Rejects Joint Opposition With PDS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004112694 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1101 GMT 
20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Italian Popular Party [PPI] has rejected the 
invitation made yesterday by Achille Occhetto [secretary of the 
Party of the Democratic Left -- PDS] to form a common opposition 
front. The news was revealed in a communique by Rosa Russo 
Jervolino. 
  "What makes our opposition different, she explained, is its 
sense of responsibility. It will be orientated toward the 
common good (we are not part of the culture of extremism) and it 
will have the capacity of making serious counterproposals. It 
is for these reasons and because of their substantial ambiguity 
that the invitation to join the PDS has received our courteous 
but firm rejection." 

</TEXT>

