<H3> <TI>   Police Make Arrests in Mafia Crackdown </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Make Arrests in Mafia Crackdown </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1804122594 Paris AFP in English 0859 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1804122594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Milan, April 18 (AFP) -- Italian police arrested 
about 100 people Monday [18 April] in a massive crackdown 
against the Mafia in the Milan region, authorities here 
announced. 
  They said some 1,000 officers were involved in the ongoing 
operation dubbed Scorched Earth and were expected to serve a 
total of 140 arrest warrants in the region. 
  Search warrants have also allowed police to seize hundreds 
of 
weapons, including machine guns and pistols, authorities said. 
  The suspects are allegedly involved in drug trafficking and 
belonging to organized crime. 

</TEXT>

