<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Solana Criticizes U.S., Russian Moves on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Solana Criticizes U.S., Russian Moves on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904153994 Madrid TVE Internacional Television in Spanish 
1300 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid TVE Internacional Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Quotation marks denote recorded passages] </F>
  [Text] In parliament today Foreign Minister Javier Solana 
criticized the leading role of Russia and the United States in 
the international action for solving the conflict in former 
Yugoslavia. According to Javier Solana, Clinton and Yeltsin's 
policy of halting air strikes signaled a go-ahead to the Serbs, 
implying that they could continue their actions in Gorazde. 
Solana also said that the presence of Spanish soldiers in the 
area depends on how the conflict develops. 
  [Correspondent Durban] Spain is willing for its blue helmets 
to remain as long as the Bosnian, Croat, and Serb communities 
are willing to live in harmony. This was stated by Javier 
Solana today in parliament. It is interpreted as meaning that 
Spain is still in favor of a political solution to the Balkan 
conflict. 
  [Solana] "I think that the Spaniards have no reason to feel 
humiliated by what is happening. Our role is being carried out 
with dignity." 
  [Durban] Today the gradual replacement of the Madrid Group 
went on with another 300 blue helmets leaving Seville for Bosnia. 
  [Colonel Pedro Brana of Cordoba Group] "The mission is the 
same as the one that is being carried out right now. What can 
change are the commitments, they change according to the 
specific moment." 
  [Durban] "As was the case before, several women officers are 
responsible for the health and psychological care of the 
contingent." 
  [Lieutenant Iris Ruiz] "I belong to the psychiatric group. I 
have a diploma in psychology, and we are going to provide 
support for the troops and for all the personnel." 
  [Durban] A further 500 blue helmets will travel to Bosnia 
over the next few days to join the Cordoba Group. 

</TEXT>

