<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Official Doubtful on Agreement by Deadline </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Official Doubtful on Agreement by Deadline </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2004113594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2004113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The United States maintains its hopes that progress 
can be achieved on the confidence-building measures, but doubts 
whether this progress can be achieved by the end of April, as 
stipulated in the latest report from UN Secretary General Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali and the Security Council's letter to the secretary 
general. This position was expressed by a U.S. official to a 
CyBC [Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation] correspondent in New York. 
  In the meantime, Robert Lamb, the U.S. State Department's 
special coordinator on Cyprus, will meet Saturday [23 April] 
with Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's special 
representative in Cyprus, to review the proximity talks on the 
confidence-building measures. The meeting will take place in 
view of Clark's visit to Nicosia next week. 

</TEXT>

