<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Says EU Aid to North `Unacceptable' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Says EU Aid to North `Unacceptable' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1904202294 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1900 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1904202294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis called upon the 
European Union [EU] to set a date for the beginning of accession 
negotiations with Cyprus. He said this decision is necessary 
and may create new dynamics for a Cyprus solution. 
  Addressing the Cyprus-EU Association Council in Luxembourg 
tonight, Mikhailidhis stressed the need for the balanced 
expansion of the Twelve to the south with the accession of 
selected Mediterranean countries such as Cyprus. The foreign 
minister asked the EU to improve trade relations, particularly 
regarding Cypriot agricultural products, by extending the 
exports calendar and increasing the percentages. He also asked 
for broad Cypriot participation in EU programs. Mikhailidhis 
suggested tripartite cooperation programs between Cyprus, EU, 
and the Middle East. 
  Referring to the issue of the EU providing financial support 
for the occupied areas in an effort to balance development 
throughout Cyprus, the foreign minister said this could only 
happen after a Cyprus solution and with the consent of the 
Cyprus Government and through it. He stressed that providing 
financial aid before a solution is an act dangerously close to 
being illegal and supportive of separation, and, therefore, it 
is unacceptable. 

</TEXT>

