<H3> <TI>   Chief Prosecutor Concludes Erbakan Committed Crime </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chief Prosecutor Concludes Erbakan Committed Crime </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1904191594 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1904191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] The Ankara chief public prosecutor has concluded 
that the remarks made by Prosperity Party leader Necmettin 
Erbakan at a party meeting last Wednesday [13 April] fall within 
the scope the crime of overtly instigating the people to hatred 
and hostility by discriminating against religion, race, or sect 
-- a crime cited in the Turkish Penal Code. The chief public 
prosecutor handed the file over to the chief prosecutor of the 
Ankara State Security Court. 
  In a statement to Turkish Radio and Television, Ankara Chief 
Public Prosecutor Nazmi Sarvan said that his office completed 
the investigation into the tape of a speech delivered by Erbakan 
at a party meeting on 13 April. We concluded, Sarvan said, that 
Erbakan's remarks constitute instigating people to hatred and 
hostility. 
  Recalling that this crime falls within the jurisdiction of 
the state security courts, Sarvan said that the file has been 
sent over to the chief prosecutor of the Ankara State Security 
Court. 
  Nusret Demirel, chief prosecutor of the Ankara State 
Security 
Court, said that the file has not reached him yet, and that his 
office is also conducting an investigation into the same issue. 
He went on to say that the two files will be joined, and the 
investigation continued. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

