  [Text] Berlin -- Federal President Richard von Weizsaecker 
has called the Serb attackers of the Muslim enclave of Gorazde 
"mere war criminals that have lost the last bit of credibility." 
He called for "a clear and firm position by the international 
organizations and their leading member countries." Chancellor 
Helmut Kohl and Russian President Boris Yeltsin have discussed 
the situation in Gorazde on the telephone. Government spokesman 
Dieter Vogel said the topics discussed were a solution through 
negotiations and a cease-fire. 

