<H3> <TI>   Bosnians Demonstrate in Bonn for NATO Help </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bosnians Demonstrate in Bonn for NATO Help </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004102294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0946 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004102294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Bosnian refugees demonstrated in 
Bonn on Wednesday [20 April] in favor of "immediate 
intervention" by NATO in Gorazde. The Society for Threatened 
Peoples organized the vigils in front of the embassies of Great 
Britain, Russia, and the United States, as well as other places. 
The Society says that about 400 people joined the 
demonstrations. 
  Tilman Zuelch, chairman of the Society, demanded the calling 
of a special session of the North Atlantic council. He stressed 
that "the ending of the genocide in Bosnia should not be left to 
the United Nations any longer." Without NATO intervention the 
70,000 trapped Bosnians in Gorazde will be "destroyed" by Serb 
troops. In addition, Zuelch demanded a special Bundestag 
session on the situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

