BFN 

  [Text] Finnish Prime Minister Esko Aho said Tuesday [19 
April] that Finland could offer its good offices in helping to 
settle the dispute between Russia and Estonia over the 
withdrawal of Russian troops still stationed in that country. 
On Monday the visiting Speaker of the Russian Duma Ivan Rybkin 
stated that Finland should act as a mediator between Russia and 
the Baltic states. Speaking to newsmen in Helsinki, Prime 
Minister Aho urged Russia and Estonia to find a settlement to 
their differences on the issue, but added that if both sides 
want help with negotiations, Finland could provide its services. 

</TEXT>

