<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Demirel Warns Against Depreciation of Lira </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Demirel Warns Against Depreciation of Lira </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1704064494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1704064494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Replying to journalists' 
questions on the economy, President Suleyman Demirel said that 
the Turkish economy does not have a structural problem, that 
there is investment, production, and exports. Turkey has 
accumulated a certain amount of internal and external debt, he 
said, and the interest on these debts is hurting Turkey's public 
finance. This is not such a strange situation, he said, and the 
state takes the necessary measures. 
  Demirel went on to say: I insist that the basis of the 
monetary problem in Turkey today is the citizens' lack of trust 
in their own money. I call on my people to trust the Turkish 
lira. As long as you run away from your own currency by buying 
U.S. dollars or other currencies, you will continue to 
depreciate your own currency. 

</TEXT>

