<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Calls For New UN Resolution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Calls For New UN Resolution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804121494 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 
1100 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1804121494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [Excerpt] Earlier today, Foreign Minister Alain 
Juppe clarified the government's position on Bosnia. He said 
one can speak of a failure by the United Nations, but this does 
not mean giving up. Philippe Harrouard reports from the Foreign 
Ministry: 
  [Harrouard] A failure by the United Nations, a challenge to 
the international community: As usual, the Serbs are playing a 
double game, but we must neither give up, nor call for 
escalation. Alain Juppe was bitter when he received us this 
morning. The minister added: No withdrawal of UN troops, no 
lifting of the arms embargo, and let's stop shilly-shallying and 
going it alone -- an allusion to the United States and Russia. 
Specifically, the United Nations must vote for a cease-fire and 
a withdrawal of the Serbs from Gorazde. 
  [Begin Juppe recording] We cannot accept the violation of 
international law, which is clear in Gorazde, as a result of 
Serb aggression. Therefore, the Security Council must order a 
cease-fire, as we have asked, a withdrawal of Serb forces, an 
exclusion zone, and the deployment of UNPROFOR [UN Protection 
Force]. We believe that such a resolution by the Security 
Council can be voted on forthwith. I cannot see who could 
oppose it today. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

