<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Corsican Installations Bombed Ahead of Leotard Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Corsican Installations Bombed Ahead of Leotard Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704102794 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 0700 
17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At 0300 this morning in Corsica, there were two 
simultaneous explosions 100 km apart. A grenade exploded in 
front of a police station at Pietrodicerce, and a powerful bomb 
went off outside the Solenzara military base near Bastia. This 
is the first time the bombers manage to get within the perimeter 
fence, which is surrounded by barbed wire and watchtowers. 
Christophe Lurie reports from Bastia: 
  [Lurie] The bomb was placed within the perimeter of the 
Solenzara military base, an hour's drive from Bastia. The 
explosion, which took place at 0300 this morning, caused 
significant damage to the office of the commander of the air 
base. Colonel Jackie Cognet had already been the target of a 
previous attack. On Friday [15 April] night, a grenade was 
thrown at his home from a vehicle, but did not caused any 
damage. These two attacks could be linked to tomorrow's visit to 
Corsica by Defense Minister Francois Leotard, who will be in 
Ajaccio to present the results achieved over the past year by 
the Balladur Government. 

</TEXT>

