<F P=101> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll: Majority Oppose More Troops for Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll: Majority Oppose More Troops for Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2004141694 Groot-Bijgaarden DE STANDAARD in Dutch 20 Apr 
94 p 5 </F>

<F P=103> BR2004141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Groot-Bijgaarden DE STANDAARD </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Flanders and Rwanda"] </F>
  [Text] The majority of Flemings do not want Belgium to send 
soldiers to Rwanda anymore. Still, our country should not 
abandon Africa, and Rwanda in particular. This was revealed by 
a poll of 499 people in Flanders conducted by Dimarso-Gallup. 
In spite of the deaths of 10 Belgian blue helmets, a small 
majority believes that Belgium should continue to provide 
military personnel for future UN peacekeeping operations. Most 
Flemings agree that our country should accept political refugees 
from Rwanda and maintain its development aid to the former 
mandated territory. 

</TEXT>

