<H3> <TI>   D66 Most Popular Party Among Students </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    D66 Most Popular Party Among Students </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2004145194 Amsterdam DE VOLKSKRANT in Dutch 20 Apr 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> BR2004145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amsterdam DE VOLKSKRANT </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Democrats 66 Scoring Highest Among </F>
Students"] 
  [Excerpt] Apparently, Netherlands students are no longer 
adhering to ideologies. Indeed, if the Netherlands were one big 
university, the D66 [Democrats 66] would be the biggest party 
and [D66 leader] Hans van Mierlo would be the unchallenged 
leader. 
  This was revealed by a representative sample conducted among 
the future generation of intellectuals by Specifiek Universitair 
Magazine (SUM). Another remarkable fact, especially in 
comparison with the 60's, is that the PvdA [Labor Party] would 
be wiped out. 
  The figures: The D66 gets almost 30 percent of the student 
votes, the VVD [People's Party for Freedom and Democracy] 19 
percent, the GroenLinks [Green Left] 13 percent, the CDA 
[Christian Democratic Appeal] 12 percent, and the PvdA only 5 
percent. The students make a fairly conscious choice. Almost 
half of them determine their choice based on a party's ideas and 
principles. This is what should alarm the PvdA most. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

