<F P=100> UNITED KINGDOM </F>
<H3> <TI>   Singapore Prime Minister Arrives for Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Singapore Prime Minister Arrives for Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1804115994 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1804115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong, who is in London on a 
three-day official visit, is holding talks with his counterpart 
John Major. 
  Earlier, Mr. Goh laid a wreath at the tomb of the unknown 
soldiers in Westminister Abbey and was given a ceremonial 
welcome at the Foreign and Commonwealth Office. 
  This is Mr. Goh's first trip to Briatin as prime minister. 
Mr. Major will host a lunch at Downing Street in Mr. Goh's 
honor. 
  Mr. Goh, whose delegation includes senior cabinet ministers 
and a high-powered business group, will be promoting Singapore 
as a business hub to potential European investors. 
  The highlight of his trip will be the Singapore Forum 
tomorrow, where he will be addressing the captains of British 
and European industries. 

</TEXT>

