<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy Criticizes Anti-Turkish TV </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoy Criticizes Anti-Turkish TV </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1904200094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1540 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1904200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, Germany April 09 (A.A.) -- Turkish ambassador 
to Germany Onur Oymen said today that the friendly feelings of 
Turks are being damaged continuously by the German media. 
  Speaking at a "roundtable meeting" led by Chancellor Helmut 
Kohl and which aimed at preventing xenophobia, Oymen said that a 
number of German TV stations broadcast anti-Turkish programs. 
  Oymen said that 2 million Turks were living in this country 
and the programs against their homeland hurt their feelings. 
  "These broadcasts are one-sided and the same old archive 
films are shown again and again, hurting the pride of Turks," he 
said. 

</TEXT>

