<H3> <TI>   Visit by Pakistan's Bhutto to Bonn Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit by Pakistan's Bhutto to Bonn Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Economic Agreement Signed </H4>

<F P=102> BK2104021594 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2104021594 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan and Germany signed an agreement on economic 
cooperation under which Germany will provide assistance worth 85 
million marks [DM] to Pakistan for various projects in the 
social sector. The agreement was signed in Bonn yesterday. 
This assistance will be in addition to the DM190.4 million 
pledged by Germany, which has not yet been utilized. German 
State Secretary (Jargon Trunk) said this agreement reflects the 
desire of the German Government to play its role in the economic 
development of Pakistan, especially in the sectors identified as 
priority sectors by the Benazir Bhutto government. 

</TEXT>

