<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visit by Pakistan's Bhutto to Bonn Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit by Pakistan's Bhutto to Bonn Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Bhutto Addresses Parliament Committee </H4>

<F P=102> BK2104035894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2104035894 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Addressing the German parliament's Economic Affairs 
Committee in Bonn today, Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto urged the 
German parliament members to play their role to resolve the 
Kashmir issue so that the amount expended for arms and 
ammunition can be spent on development. The prime minister said 
if a settlement to the Kashmir dispute is achieved, all other 
issues between Pakistan and India will also be resolved. 
Referring to the 20-percent increase in the Indian defense 
budget, the prime minister said it is basically aimed at 
crushing the freedom movement in occupied Kashmir. 
Nevertheless, this increase has also put pressure on Pakistan 
to take appropriate steps to deal with any threat to its 
security. The prime minister said Pakistan had made several 
proposals to India for mutual reduction of forces, for reducing 
defense expenditure, for preventing nuclear proliferation and an 
arms race, and for resolving the Kashmir dispute, but India has 
not demonstrated any positive reaction to any of these issues. 
  Referring to internal affairs, the prime minister said her 
government has granted several concessions that ensure extensive 
opportunities to foreign investors in Pakistan. She said all 
foreign investors are totally safe in Pakistan, as the benefit 
of nationalizing institutions in the current age of market 
economy has ended. German investors can play a dominant role in 
Pakistan's development. The prime minister said Pakistan's 
territory is extremely attractive and profitable for investors 
as its economy is progressing toward stability. The country is 
replete with natural resources and the best business 
opportunities are available here due to its location in an 
important region of the world. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

