<H3> <TI>   Visit by Pakistan's Bhutto to Bonn Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit by Pakistan's Bhutto to Bonn Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Asif Ali, Kinkel Hold Talks </H4>

<F P=102> BK2104040594 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2104040594 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The foreign ministers of Pakistan and Germany held 
detailed discussion in Bonn today on a number of issues of 
mutual concern and of regional and international importance. 
Later, Pakistan Foreign Minister Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali told 
Radio Pakistan's special representative that he had informed Mr. 
Kinkel of Pakistan's sincere desire to amicably resolve the 
Kashmir problem and normalize its relations with India. But, he 
said, India has not responded positively to various proposals 
presented by Pakistan to realize this objective. Mr. Kinkel 
said Germany was fully aware of the situation in Indian-held 
Kashmir and the importance of the Kashmir dispute in 
Pakistan-India relations. He assured that Germany would make 
efforts to persuade India to find a peaceful solution of the 
Kashmir problem. Mr. Kinkel was also briefed on Pakistan's 
efforts to bring about peace in Afghanistan, Tajikistan, and 
Somalia. 

</TEXT>

