<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Urges Russia To Use Hermes Guarantees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Urges Russia To Use Hermes Guarantees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104115394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1109 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow (DDP/ADN) -- German Economics Minister 
Guenter Rexrodt urged Russia to make full use of the Hermes 
guarantees for trade with Germany. The survival of many German 
firms, especially in the former East Germany, depends on this, 
Rexrodt told journalists after a talk with his Russian 
counterpart Aleksandr Shokhin in Moscow today. 
  Hermes credits total 2.5 billion marks [DM] this year. 
Shokhin pointed out that Russia "is subject both to internal 
restrictions and IMF conditions with regard to debts." 
  Rexrodt called on German industry to invest in Russia 
despite 
all the difficulties there. It must not miss the right 
opportunity to "gain a foothold on the Russian market and its 
great potential." He conveyed to Shokhin the wish felt by many 
German businessmen "for greater clarity and predictability in 
Russia, among other things in the tax system and in granting 
export licenses," Rexrodt said. He added that Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin's upcoming visit to Germany in mid-May and 
preparations for the next session of the German-Russian 
Cooperation Council in St. Petersburg were also discussed. 
  Rexrodt arrived in Moscow last night for a one-day visit. He 
is to hold talks with Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin 
this afternoon. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

