<H3> <TI>   Satisfied With PRC Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Satisfied With PRC Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004210394 Lisbon RTP Internacional Television in 
Portuguese 1811 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RTP Internacional Television </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cavaco Silva is on his way back to Lisbon, having 
spent the last few hours of his 11-day Far East tour in Hong 
Kong. It was in Hong Kong that the prime minister quantified 
the economic results of the contacts established in China and 
Macao, specifically business deals worth over 100 million contos 
[1 conto equals 1,000 escudos]. 
  [Announcer] Cavaco Silva's meeting with the governor of Hong 
Kong was the last official act of the prime minister's 11-day 
visit to China. Cavaco is now on his way home, but while still 
in Hong Kong he made an appraisal of his trip and declared 
himself very pleased. The visit achieved all the objectives we 
set ourselves, the prime minister stated, and proceeded to 
justify his statement with the economic results: The 60 
Portuguese businessmen who travelled with the head of the 
government left China with 100 million contos' worth of 
contracts either signed or under negotiation, 25 millions 
corresponding to deals already guaranteed between Portuguese and 
Chinese companies, and the remainder still dependent on further 
talks. This represents a degree of Sino-Portuguese economic 
cooperation that has surpassed the best expectations of the 
Portuguese delegation. 

</TEXT>

