<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Reiterates Support for UN Document </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Reiterates Support for UN Document </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1904202994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1600 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1904202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis has said 
the Cypriot Government has not been sounded out on any changes 
to the 21 March UN document on the confidence-building measures. 
He added that the position of the Greek Cypriot side is that it 
accepts the document as is, while Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf 
Denktas is raising many points other than the issue of access to 
Famagusta. 
  The spokesman stressed that Kliridhis is ready to meet 
either 
with Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's special 
representative in Cyprus, or Gustave Feissel, the UN secretary 
general's alternate special representative in Cyprus, to 
reiterate that he has accepted the document as is and expects 
the Turkish side to do the same. Kasoulidhis concluded that the 
president is ready to say that he will accept neither new 
documents nor a modification of the current document. 

</TEXT>

