<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 20 (AA) -- Turkey is against any kind 
of forceful border changing policy, the Foreign Ministry said on 
Wednesday [20 April]. 
  Foreign Ministry spokesman Ferhat Ataman said at his weekly 
briefing that a draft was signed by the 11-nation Minsk Group in 
an effort to find a solution to the problem in Nagorno-Karabakh, 
during their meeting in Prague on April 11-15. 
  Ataman said it is the second document signed after the Rome 
Agreement, adding that it is very important that free exchange 
of ideas can be held between representatives of conflicting 
sides. 
  He said that Armenia should give up its new offensive 
against 
Azerbaijan, which is a violation of UN, CSCE and other 
international norms. 
  Ataman renewed Turkey's support for Azerbaijan's violated 
territorial unity. 

</TEXT>

