<F P=102>   TA2004125794 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1030 GMT 20 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2004125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkey's main opposition party, the Motherland Party 
[ANAP], has submitted a motion to the Turkish Grand National 
Assembly [TGNA] to hold a general debate on the latest 
developments regarding Cyprus. The motion refers to reports 
that during Prime Minister Ciller's recent visit to the United 
States, President Clinton pressured her in connection with the 
Cyprus question. ANAP said: It is inconceivable to accept such 
behavior, which means that our foreign policy is under foreign 
domination regarding a national issue such as Cyprus. The prime 
minister herself must urgently clarify this issue before the 
TGNA. 
  ANAP said the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus [TRNC], 
which has been living in peace for a long time, is recently 
being pushed toward chaos, step by step. It claimed that the 
debates being held at the United Nations are nothing but efforts 
to exert pressure on the TRNC delegation and Turkey. ANAP also 
charged that the government program does not pay enough 
attention to the issue of the TRNC. 

