<H3> <TI>   Police Uncover Group Planning To Kill Politicians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Uncover Group Planning To Kill Politicians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2004165494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1515 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2004165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 20 (AA) -- Interior Minister Nahit 
Mentese said today that a new organization named the 
`Resalvation Union' which was planning to assassinate ranking 
officials and politicians, has been revealed. 
  During a meeting of the parliament's interior commission, 
Mentese said that police were working under great risk and are 
revealing many incidents. 
  Mentese said that the `Resalvation Union' was revealed when 
police teams Tuesday [19 April] caught five members of the 
organization, five minutes before their attempt to rob a bank in 
the Zeytinburnu township of Istanbul. 
  The men were caught with three automatic guns, two 
revolvers, 
three hand grenades. 

</TEXT>

