<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis said that he is in 
continuous contact with Greek Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou, 
who is on an official visit to the United States. The last 
briefing, he added, took place last night during a telephone 
conversation in which they discussed the latest developments in 
the Cyprus issue. 
  President Kliridhis made the above remarks this morning at 
Larnaca Airport before departing for Bucharest, Romania. In 
Bucharest, the president will address a seminar on the political 
and economic developments in the Black Sea, Mediterranean and 
surrounding countries. President Kliridhis also noted that Joe 
Clark, UN secretary general's special representative in Cyprus, 
will go to Ankara on Sunday [24 April] in an attempt to mobilize 
Turkey regarding its influence on Rauf Denktas. He also said 
that Clark will come to Cyprus next Wednesday. 
  In Bucharest, President Kliridhis will also have talks with 
Romanian President Ion Iliescu, during which they will examine 
issues of telecommunications and economic cooperation between 
Cyprus and Romania. President Kliridhis will return to Cyprus 
tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

