<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Urges Prompt NATO Decision on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Urges Prompt NATO Decision on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2004155094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1455 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2004155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 20 (AA) -- Foreign Ministry spokesman 
Ferhat Ataman said today that to prevent further deaths in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, the North Atlantic Treaty Organization 
should make a decision promptly. 
  Ataman told a weekly press conference that the UN secretary 
general had authorized the alliance to carry out air strikes not 
only to protect Gorazde, but Zepa, Srebrenica, Tuzla, Bihac and 
Sarajevo. 
  "Even though it's late, we regard this initiative as a 
positive and useful step," Ataman said. 
  Ataman pointed out that UN Resolutions 824 and 836 had 
empowered the UN secretary general to make such a demand. 
  "An urgent initiative to be taken by NATO in line with this 
call is necessary to protect the organization's respectability, 
effectiveness and deterrence," he concluded. 

</TEXT>

